      "writtenOn": "2020-10-28T15:09:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, an FMA always works as if,\n\n   infinite_precision_float p \u003d x*y;\n   return (float)(p + z);\n\nit\u0027s usually, but not quite always, the same result you\u0027d get by doing\n\n   double p \u003d x*y;\n   return (float)(p + z);\n\nPrecision is not my main concern with these types of underspecified functions... it\u0027s the unpredictability.  We\u0027ve had bugs with expressions like sqrt(1-fma(...)) where everything is fine when fused (or unfused) but explodes when unfused (or fused).  Same for rsqrt, rcp.",
      "parentUuid": "e4785767_1d1d3965",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 20,
        "endChar": 32
      },
      "revId": "8769906c220cf2ed3c00386301d8f7090422c2f3",
